{
  "texts": [
    "Although zero-shot generalizability is often observed to a certain extent, a gap from perfect generalization typically remains.",
    "To bridge this gap, we fine-tune the models using data from the downstream tasks.",
    "A stronger generalizability in a pre-trained model implies that less data is required during fine-tuning, leading to higher sample efficiency.",
    "The reduction in sample size relative to training a model from scratch quantifies the advantage of employing a multi-task pre-trained model.",
    "The sampling efficiency of the pre-trained DPA-2 on downstream tasks was evaluated by comparing it against various other DP models that were trained from scratch."
  ]
}